summary: Licensed United Healthcare Insurance Sales Agent with a proven track record in sales and customer service, skilled at upselling/cross-selling health insurance products, building strong client relationships, and delivering exceptional service while meeting or exceeding goals.

experience.title: Licensed United Healthcare Insurance Sales Agent
experience.description: Provided services to clients changing or updating healthcare insurance needs by upselling/cross-selling a variety of health insurance products (MA, MAPD, MED Sup and PDPs) for groups and individual consumers; assisted with outbound campaigns to ensure customer satisfaction; demonstrated prospecting skills; met/exceeded sales goals; built new client relationships with strong people skills and product knowledge while maintaining HIPAA compliance and company policy.

experience.title: Account Executive Sales Agent/FedEx Account
experience.description: Maintained and deepened existing customer relations; made outbound calls to engage customers with new products and services to develop value propositions; increased volume from existing customers; delivered client services using effective negotiation and collaboration; conducted daily rapport-building with customers using a consultative sales approach and maintained regular contact with designated accounts.

experience.title: Licensed United Healthcare Insurance Sales Agent
experience.description: Provided services to clients updating healthcare insurance needs by upselling/cross-selling health insurance products (MA, MAPD, MED Sup and PDPs) for groups and individuals; assisted with outbound campaigns; demonstrated prospecting skills; built new client relationships with strong people skills and product knowledge while gaining customer trust and rapport; followed HIPAA guidelines and company policy.

experience.title: Customer Service Agent
experience.description: Handled pharmacy/pharmacist contacts via telephone regarding insurance authorization, benefits, claims, and general assistance; resolved adjudicated prescription claims related to member eligibility and prior authorizations/ overrides; delivered exceptional customer service in a fast-paced environment while adhering to HIPAA and CMS compliance.

experience.title: Online Customer Service & Sales Agent/ Web/Ivr PSR II
experience.description: Provided inbound calls to assist personal and business customers with website navigation, troubleshooting and account maintenance; established online accounts, password resets, and user IDs; managed online bill pay issues; reconciling accounts using Quicken and QuickBooks; educated and referred all product/services; achieved first-contact resolutions and ensured regulatory compliance (BSA, USA PATRIOT Act, OFAC, FDIC, TISA, HMDA, CRA).

experience.title: Customer Service Task Specialist
experience.description: Made contact with creditors and new/existing clients to open/update accounts; negotiated terms; updated and modified payables; collected and processed payments; achieved quota goals of 200 inbound/outbound calls daily; collaborated with customer care departments to enhance service.
